# Build and Development Setup

## Required Tools
- Visual Studio Code with PlatformIO extension

## Building the Firmware
1. Open the `firmware` directory in VS Code with PlatformIO
2. Select your board configuration from the PlatformIO Project Tasks
3. Build and upload the firmware

## File Storage
- SD Card: Format with FAT32 and place game files in the root directory
- Flash Storage: Place files in [firmware/data/](mdc:firmware/data/) and use PlatformIO to upload
